  "observation": "Domain sevo-life (fitness 0.702) generated 2 insights",
  "suggestion": "Efficiency = resources gained / energy burned. Current genomes over-explore and over-produce trails relative to harvest; shift to conservation-first, goal-directed movement.; Efficiency is the critical bottleneck at 0.145 (contributing only 0.029 to overall score). This indicates entities are burning energy on movement and trail production without sufficient resource harvest return. Root causes: (1) energyConserve is low on some genomes (0.65-0.7 vs achievable 0.9), (2) moveSpeed is high on expensive explorers (0.7 on aesthetic entity), (3) trail intensity costs energy without direct survival benefit. Fix: uniformly raise energyConserve to 0.8+ on low performers, reduce moveSpeed by 5-10% to cut baseline burn, lower trail intensity on non-critical entities. Expected impact: efficiency 0.145 → 0.25-0.3, adding ~0.04-0.05 to overall fitness.",
